• Set the program context for the interviewer with business or technical goals/drivers. 
    • Describe the end-to-end system design or architecture used and key flows;  
    • Describe  implementation and performance tradeoffs with examples;  
    • Describe potential technical risks, dependencies, improvements to the solution if done retrospectively; 
    • Describe reliability, scaling, efficiency and performance work during this project;  
    • Describe what metrics were established to set goals and measure both business and technical success;  how are these goals monitored and reported
    • Describe any major technical risks issue you encountered during this project and proactive/reactive mitigation.                                      > Demo’d rollout or launch and if any issues were found during or post launch and mitigation.
